Bungoma Governor Kenneth Lusaka has for two weeks been racing against time to launch road projects in a bid to woo voters to reelect him. He has launched six roads and two bridges for Sh410 million.They are the Lusaka Road, which will be tarmacked for Sh140 million, the Marrel-Namuyemba road for Sh72 million, Chwele for Sh35 milion, Cheptais for Sh54 million, Kapsokwony for Sh51 million and Kapkateny-Cheptonoi for Sh4 million.Other projects launched include the construction of the Masuno Bridge at Sh25 million.Yesterday, Lusaka said the projects will be completed by June next year. &ldquo;We have given the contractors strict deadlines,&rdquo; he said.